snippet.title: Pakistan Defence Day || 6th September 2021 || Cosmopolitan Grammar School || Amber Reviews
snippet.description:
The Pakistani nation paid a befitting tribute to the country's armed forces Monday, who lay down their lives for the motherland, as it observed Defence Day with traditional spirit and enthusiasm.

On September 6, 1965, the armed forces of Pakistan successfully thwarted an Indian onslaught in the dead of night. Pakistan's armed forces and their heroics helped push back the enemy in a successful defence that saw the entire nation back its troops during the war.

This year's Defense and Martyrs' Day theme is "Our martyrs our pride, salute to all the relatives belonging to ghazis and Shaheeds.”
